Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain and halve @Grilling Cheese{200%grams} lengthways. Quarter each half lengthways to make evenly sized batons.

Add to a #bowl{} of cold @water{to taste}.

Halve the @Irish Bacon{130%grams} widthways (use #scissors{} if easier), then stretch each piece slightly using the back of a #knife{}. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Remove the cheese from the water and pat dry with kitchen paper.

Wrap each grilling cheese slice with a piece of bacon. Place on a lined #baking tray{}.

Bake the bacon-wrapped cheese on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{15-20%mins}. Turn the tray halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, pop the @Aioli{1%sachet} and @Sweet Chilli Sauce{1%sachet} into a small bowl. Mix together until combined.

Once cooked, remove the cheese from the oven.

Transfer to a #serving plate{}.

Serve with the sweet chilli aioli alongside for dipping.